The US State Department has appointed Ambassador Jeff Feltman as the Special Envoy for the Horn of Africa. Feltman's role will focus on addressing the urgent crises in Ethiopia, including the withdrawal of Eritrean forces, cessation of hostilities, and ensuring humanitarian access. The US also encourages leaders of Egypt, Ethiopia, and Sudan to resolve their disputes around the Grand Ethiopia Renaissance Dam and shared water resources. The US is committed to working with allies and partners to promote peace and prosperity in the Horn of Africa.